cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the use of Prolog in Web applications, which involves handling Web documents and protocols. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for Semantic Web RDF processing, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for handling large documents efficiently, Databases (cs.DB) for parsing and representing Web document types, Software Engineering (cs.SE) for discussing development and deployment, and Programming Languages (cs.PL) for the extensions to Prolog.
